-- RAB Capital’s Joshi Poached to Head BCA’s European Strategy Team
-- B y   A d a m   H a i g h
-- 2011-01-28T07:58:26Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-01-28/rab-capital-s-joshi-poached-to-head-bca-s-european-strategy-team.html
Dhaval Joshi has left his position
as chief strategist at London-based hedge fund  RAB Capital Plc 
to join BCA Research as head of its European Investment Strategy
team, according to two people with knowledge of the move.  Joshi, who has also worked as a strategist at Societe
Generale SA in  London , will begin his new role in February, said
the people, who declined to be indentified before an official
announcement.  Charlotte Kirkham, a London-based external spokeswoman for
RAB Capital, confirmed that Joshi has left the company. Joshi
declined to comment on his reason for leaving. RAB Capital,
founded by Philip Richards and Michael Alen-Buckley, had $1.05
billion of assets under management as of Dec. 31.  A phone message left with BCA Research was not returned.
The firm is an independent provider of global investment
research based in  Montreal , according to its website.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Adam Haigh in London at 
